FBIS3-25492 "drafr035_c_94017" FBIS-AFR-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA ANC Canvassers Killed in Attack in Southern Natal MB1902092894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0900 GMT 19 Feb 94 MB1902092894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Fourteen people have been killed and two seriously wounded in an attack at Creighton in Southern Natal. Our Durban news staff reports that a group of canvassers, mainly young people, were collecting fees in preparation of an ANC [African National Congress] voter education program planned for today. The people were sleeping in a hut when they were attacked early this morning. No further details are known at this stage.
